Re: Mamorubeki?
by Hyperworm » Fri 01.23.2009 4:07 pm AJBryant wrote:A "yomubeki hon" is a "book that must be read" and a "mamorubeki mono" is a "person or thing that must be protected".Technically shouldn't that be "a book that [I] must read" and "a thing that [I] must protect"?(vs. yomarerubeki hon, mamorarerubeki mono)Not a big difference in most cases of course...For completeness's sake: "beki" can also mean "should" as well as "must".
