Re: Mamorubeki?
by Yudan Taiteki » Fri 01.23.2009 5:18 pm Hyperworm wrote:For completeness's sake: "beki" can also mean "should" as well as "must".But only when "should" is used with the meaning of "must"; "You should try the fish" would be expressed in Japanese with ほうがいい, not べき.
-Chris Kern
Yudan Taiteki
Posts: 5609Joined: Wed 11.01.2006 11:32 pm
Native language: English
